  "text": "The cardinality ♯(S(a)) = 2♯ (S 1 (a) ) is called the kissing number of a. Determination of the maximum max a∈Pn 2♯ (S 1 (a) ) is known as the lattice kissing number problem ([20, Chapter 1,  §2] ). The actual value of max a∈Pn ♯ (S 1 (a) ) is known for 1 ≤ n ≤ 9 and n = 24 (cf. [CITATION_1] ). One can prove the estimate max a∈Pn ♯(S 1 (a)) ≤ 2 n − 1 for all n as follows: Let a ∈ P n and x, y ∈ S(a). If y−x = 2z ∈ 2Z n , then m 1 (a) = t (x+2z)a(x+2z) = t xax, and hence Let w k be the dual type one class function of m k . When k ≥ 2, it is not trivial that the Hermite like constant of m k /ϕ exists for a given type one class function ϕ. We set ",
